========================================
SCREENSHOT HANDLING - REVISION NOTES
========================================

1. FULL BROWSER SCREENSHOT
--------------------------

TakesScreenshot ts = (TakesScreenshot) driver;

File src = ts.getScreenshotAs(OutputType.FILE);

File dest = new File("./Screenshots/HomePage.png");

FileHandler.copy(src, dest);

----------------------------------------

Memory Trick:

Cast Driver
Capture Screenshot
Copy Screenshot

----------------------------------------

Why Casting Required?

WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();

getScreenshotAs() belongs to TakesScreenshot Interface.

So we must cast:

(TakesScreenshot) driver

========================================

2. ELEMENT SCREENSHOT
---------------------

WebElement element =
driver.findElement(By.id("name"));

File src =
element.getScreenshotAs(OutputType.FILE);

File dest =
new File("./Screenshots/NameField.png");

FileHandler.copy(src, dest);

----------------------------------------

Memory Trick:

Find Element
Capture Screenshot
Copy Screenshot

----------------------------------------

Why Casting NOT Required?

WebElement already provides:

getScreenshotAs()

Therefore:

No TakesScreenshot Interface
No Casting Required

